body:
The SystemTap language is surprisingly similar to bpftrace, but a bit more [powerful](https://sourceware.org/systemtap/tutorial.pdf)! @laanwj I'm able to run `stap p2p_messages.stp` (as user with privileges) to hook into a running Bitcoin Core process. 

```stp
$ cat p2p_messages.stp
probe process("src/bitcoind").provider("net").mark("*bound_message") {
  if ($$name == "inbound_message") {
    printf ("<-- peer=%d %s\n", $arg1, user_string($arg4))
  } else {
    printf ("--> peer=%d %s\n", $arg1, user_string($arg4))
  }
}
```
produces output similar to:
```
...
<-- peer=1 inv
--> peer=1 getdata
<-- peer=1 tx
...
```
